<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10975] Histogram buckets exposed in jmx are sorted by count</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10975</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The estimated histogram snapshot lets its parent provide the getValues implementation which sorts the bucket array:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/dropwizard/metrics/blob/3.1-maintenance/metrics-core/src/main/java/com/codahale/metrics/UniformSnapshot.java#L25&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/dropwizard/metrics/blob/3.1-maintenance/metrics-core/src/main/java/com/codahale/metrics/UniformSnapshot.java#L25&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;making it hard to determine what count belonged to what bucket. Along with removal of the pre 2.2 deprecated metrics this makes it nearly impossible to track latencies over time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
